  "texts": [
    "But a more important intrinsic limitation is that \"symbolic value\" and \"aesthetic value\" are beyond AI's purview.",
    "These problems cannot be \"specified\"; their \"success criteria\" cannot be objectively quantified or assessed.",
    "As a result, no algorithms can be designed (Acemoglu and Autor 2011).",
    "In this respect, they are similar to \"moral worth\" or \"moral excellence,\" which largely escape AI's grasp (Sison and Redín 2023).Because they lack meaningful creativity, even \"intelligent\" robots do not have the capacity to innovate (Redín et al. 2023; Botica 2017).",
    "At most, AI is an \"efficient method of imitation\" (Mitchell 2019, 146), probabilistically identifying patterns better, faster, and cheaper (Agrawal et al. 2018)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}